		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">The Unappreciated Bow<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Feb 20th 6:01 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=9827100694532&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=9827100694532&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=9827100694532"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9827100694532></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have notice that the use of bows on Norrath, even by the class whom have so long been it's master, has been on the decline.<br><br>Many people, even fellow rangers, perhaps aren't aware of how helpful a good bow can be. Can't find a group? It's been my experience that a ranger in her early twenties to mid/late thirties can easily solo non- caster mobs considerable levels higher than she, through the use of snare, and if you're lucky, a SoW. Unlike our druid cousins however, we obviously can't rely on our spells. The combination of spells and a good bow can be quite potent. Oak grade or higher, and as low a delay as possible. While warriors, rogues, and paladins should aim for high damage bows, regardless of delay, rangers and shadowknights should look for speed and damage ratio when choosing a bow, for thier abilities to immobilize mobs requires getting in as many shots as possible. <br><br>I have seen many people pay large amounts of platinum for a Runed Oak bow, however to my knowledge you will still need to buy or make expensive silverpoint arrows to achieve the magical damage they're paying for. Darkwoods tend to have better stats, superior range, and on most servers easier to obtain, and can even be cheaper than the dropped Runed Oak. They are also useable by all of the above listed classes. Once your bow is a high enough grade, you won't need to rely so much on expensive high damage arrows.<br><br>For anyone thinking of becoming one of Norrath Woodland's finest, I suggest starting on your trueshot quest as soon as you are able. Though the stats are about the same as a darkwood, it's range is unfortunatly 50 feet less, however it's usually cheaper to obtain. Any fletcher over 165 should be able to succesfully make one, however they need to have the nodrop micro servos and dwarven wire handy to actually complete the bow. The rest of the quest is very easy, the most difficult part being the long boring boat ride from freeport, and the chasing of rouge and runaway clockworks as they madly crawl about steamfont.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
